I’m preparing the standalone Google Apps Script deployment guidance next so the testimonial webhook and Drive/Sheet workflow are fully separated from the contact system.

## Separate testimonial Apps Script deployment

Use a completely separate Apps Script project from the contact one.

### Recommended Google Sheet structure

Create a dedicated sheet named `Testimonials` with these columns:

1. Timestamp
2. Google User ID
3. Name
4. Email
5. Phone Number
6. Subject
7. Message
8. Rating
9. Uploaded File URL
10. Authentication Provider
11. Approval Status

Default value for `Approval Status`:
- `Pending`

---

## Apps Script webhook code

Paste this into a new Apps Script web app deployment:

```javascript
function doPost(e) {
  try {
    const payload = JSON.parse(e.postData.contents || "{}");

    if (
      !payload.googleUserId ||
      !payload.name ||
      !payload.email ||
      !payload.phone ||
      !payload.subject ||
      !payload.message ||
      !payload.rating
    ) {
      return ContentService
        .createTextOutput(
          JSON.stringify({ ok: false, error: "Missing required fields." })
        )
        .setMimeType(ContentService.MimeType.JSON);
    }

    const sheet = SpreadsheetApp
      .getActiveSpreadsheet()
      .getSheetByName("Testimonials");

    if (!sheet) {
      throw new Error("Testimonials sheet not found.");
    }

    const folderId = PropertiesService
      .getScriptProperties()
      .getProperty("TESTIMONIAL_DOCUMENT_FOLDER_ID");

    let uploadedFileUrl = "";

    if (payload.fileBase64 && payload.fileName && payload.fileType) {
      const blob = Utilities.newBlob(
        Utilities.base64Decode(payload.fileBase64),
        payload.fileType,
        payload.fileName
      );

      const uniqueFileName = `${Date.now()}_${payload.fileName}`;
      const folder = folderId
        ? DriveApp.getFolderById(folderId)
        : DriveApp.getRootFolder();

      const createdFile = folder.createFile(blob.setName(uniqueFileName));
      uploadedFileUrl = createdFile.getUrl();
    }

    const row = [
      new Date().toISOString(),
      payload.googleUserId,
      payload.name,
      payload.email,
      payload.phone,
      payload.subject,
      payload.message,
      Number(payload.rating),
      uploadedFileUrl,
      payload.provider || "google",
      "Pending",
    ];

    sheet.appendRow(row);

    return ContentService
      .createTextOutput(JSON.stringify({ ok: true }))
      .setMimeType(ContentService.MimeType.JSON);
  } catch (error) {
    return ContentService
      .createTextOutput(
        JSON.stringify({ ok: false, error: error.message })
      )
      .setMimeType(ContentService.MimeType.JSON);
  }
}
```

---

## Apps Script properties to set

Inside your Apps Script project, add this script property:

- `TESTIMONIAL_DOCUMENT_FOLDER_ID`

This should point to the Drive folder where uploaded reference documents will be stored.

---

## Deployment rules

- Do not reuse the contact Apps Script
- Do not reuse the contact webhook URL
- Use a separate deployment and separate Google Sheet
- Keep the webhook URL only in the server-side environment variable:
  - `TESTIMONIAL_WEBHOOK_URL`

---

## Important note

The file upload handling belongs inside Apps Script, not in Next.js. That keeps the Google Drive folder configuration inside Apps Script Properties and avoids adding Drive-related environment variables to the Next.js app.

If you want, I can next help you generate the exact Google Cloud OAuth setup checklist for the Auth.js Google provider.

